    <abstract>Appendix G contains a translation of the colophon of the carved Huayanjing in the Jinci Museum that we documented. The colophon lists names and functions of monks involved in the translation project of this 
    sutra, that was completed on September 29, 699, and headed by Siksananda. Fazang was one of the monks involved.</abstract>
